 was.","pov":"","mailout":"A look at what the coming week will bring -- and a list of recommended RANE articles from the week that was.","overview":"","youtube_video_url":"","created":"1771077600","created_formatted":"Feb 14, 2026 | 14:00 GMT","changed":"1771077627","changed_formatted":"Feb 14, 2026 | 14:00 GMT","path_alias":"article/weekly-rundown-board-peace-convenes-russia-ukraine-us-talks-geneva","article_type":{"tid":"502","vid":"30","name":"Assessments"},"assessments_type":[],"column_type":[],"media_type":[],"global_perspectives_type":[],"sectioned_content_type":[],"forecast_type":[],"www_public_postings_type":[],"source":"","www_site_page_type":[],"taxonomy":[{"tid":"59","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"United States","code":"US","path_alias":"/region/americas/united-states"},{"tid":"127","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Israel","code":"IL","path_alias":"/region/middle-east-and-north-africa/israel"},{"tid":"133","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Palestinian Territories","code":"PS","path_alias":"/region/middle-east-and-north-africa/palestinian-territories"},{"tid":"199","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Indonesia","code":"ID","path_alias":"/region/asia-pacific/indonesia"},{"tid":"221","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Vietnam","code":"VN","path_alias":"/region/asia-pacific/vietnam"},{"tid":"95","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Slovakia","code":"SK","path_alias":"/region/europe/slovakia"},{"tid":"77","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Hungary","code":"HU","path_alias":"/region/europe/hungary"},{"tid":"113","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Ukraine","code":"UA","path_alias":"/region/eurasia/ukraine"},{"tid":"110","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Russia","code":"RU","path_alias":"/region/eurasia/russia"},{"tid":"118","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"India","code":"IN","path_alias":"/region/south-asia/india"},{"tid":"1848","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Israel-Hamas Conflict","path_alias":"/topic/israel-hamas-conflict"},{"tid":"529","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Military \u0026 Security","path_alias":"/topic/military-security"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Politics","path_alias":"/topic/politics"},{"tid":"1840","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Russia-Ukraine Conflict","path_alias":"/topic/russia-ukraine-conflict"}],"author":[],"pdf":"","status":1,"premium":1,"countries":[{"tid":"59","vid":"5","name":"United States"},{"tid":"127","vid":"5","name":"Israel"},{"tid":"133","vid":"5","name":"Palestinian Territories"},{"tid":"199","vid":"5","name":"Indonesia"},{"tid":"221","vid":"5","name":"Vietnam"},{"tid":"95","vid":"5","name":"Slovakia"},{"tid":"77","vid":"5","name":"Hungary"},{"tid":"113","vid":"5","name":"Ukraine"},{"tid":"110","vid":"5","name":"Russia"},{"tid":"118","vid":"5","name":"India"}],"wv_topics":[{"tid":"1848","vid":"33","name":"Israel-Hamas Conflict"},{"tid":"529","vid":"33","name":"Military \u0026 Security"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","name":"Politics"},{"tid":"1840","vid":"33","name":"Russia-Ukraine Conflict"}],"is_bookmarked":0},{"nid":"352023","type":"article","ntype":"worldview","title":"Bangladesh Nationalist Party Wins Big in First Election Since 2024 Uprising","promo_image":{"uri":"public://GettyImages-2260838506 (1).jpg","alt":"A man walks past campaign posters of Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) chairman and Tarique Rahman in Dhaka on Feb. 13, 2026.","title":"A man walks past campaign posters of Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) chairman and Tarique Rahman in Dhaka on Feb. 13, 2026.","caption":"A man walks past campaign posters of Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) chairman and Tarique Rahman in Dhaka on Feb. 13, 2026.","credit":"(Sajjad HUSSAIN / AFP via Getty Images)","sizes":{"16x9":{"tiny":"16x9_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=d-MzaKNt","small":"16x9_small/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=9O7YZMje","medium":"16x9_medium/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=pR7mTi6M","large":"16x9_large/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=2eXfIe25","full":"16x9_full/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=x6TUbV7a"},"square":{"tiny":"square_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=sz-jyUye","small":"square_small/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=1jg7ZNkA","medium":"square_medium/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=VEBhU4QG","large":"square_large/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=pSPPYdnq","full":"square_full/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=bEc-aHdv"},"article":{"tiny":"article_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=tfPYWcqI","small":"article_small/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=x__RaAM6","medium":"article_medium/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=3cQ0Jlgn","large":"article_large/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=LpMOzfUW","full":"article_full/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=_BpDUpt9"},"2x1":{"tiny":"2x1_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=NOtA60WM","small":"2x1_small/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=jY5ySjns","medium":"2x1_medium/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=XKjS2eY_","large":"2x1_large/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=gGXtqfc_","full":"2x1_full/public/GettyImages-2260838506%20%281%29.jpg?itok=V-_Az0ZM"}}},"teaser_body":"The transition from an interim administration will likely restore political stability, though social and fiscal pressures will still pose constraints for the new center-right government.","pov":"","mailout":"The Bangladesh Nationalist Party's election victory will strengthen political stability, while its legislative supermajority will enable the party to advance constitutional and economic reforms and pursue a foreign policy that balances ties with India and China; however, social and fiscal pressures will constrain its efforts to reform the country in the wake of the 2024 revolution. On Feb. 13, the center-right Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) announced that it won Bangladesh's Feb. 12 parliamentary elections, positioning its leader, Tarique Rahman, the son of the late former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia, to assume the premiership. As of Feb. 13, the Election Commission had not yet published the official results, but several local media outlets report that the party surpassed the 151-seat threshold needed for a simple majority in the 350-member parliament, winning an estimated 209 general seats that, when combined with seats allocated after results are confirmed, give the BNP a two-thirds supermajority. The other main contender was an Islamist party, Jamaat-e-Islami, which participated as part of an 11-party alliance that cumulatively only won an estimated 74 seats. Once the Election Commission publishes the official gazette, newly elected members of parliament are required to take their oaths within three days, formally transferring power from an interim government that has led the country for the past year and a half and enabling the formation of the new government. Alongside the parliamentary vote, Bangladeshis also approved a referendum on the interim government's proposed constitutional reforms. While this carries significant political weight and will pressure lawmakers to enact the reforms, the outcome is legally non-binding and still requires parliamentary approval to take effect.","overview":"","youtube_video_url":"","created":"1771019311","created_formatted":"Feb 13, 2026 | 21:48 GMT","changed":"1771019311","changed_formatted":"Feb 13, 2026 | 21:48 GMT","path_alias":"article/bangladesh-nationalist-party-wins-big-first-election-2024-uprising","article_type":{"tid":"502","vid":"30","name":"Assessments"},"assessments_type":[],"column_type":[],"media_type":[],"global_perspectives_type":[],"sectioned_content_type":[],"forecast_type":[],"www_public_postings_type":[],"source":"","www_site_page_type":[],"taxonomy":[{"tid":"116","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Bangladesh","code":"BD","path_alias":"/region/south-asia/bangladesh"},{"tid":"528","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Economics","path_alias":"/topic/economics"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Politics","path_alias":"/topic/politics"}],"author":[],"pdf":"","status":1,"premium":1,"countries":[{"tid":"116","vid":"5","name":"Bangladesh"}],"wv_topics":[{"tid":"528","vid":"33","name":"Economics"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","name":"Politics"}],"is_bookmarked":0},{"nid":"290404","type":"article","ntype":"worldview","title":"Geopolitical Calendar","promo_image":{"uri":"public://Geopolitical Calendar Display 02212025 (1).png","alt":"","title":"","caption":"","credit":"","sizes":{"16x9":{"tiny":"16x9_tiny/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=T9P3aalD","small":"16x9_small/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=5LXK3mLR","medium":"16x9_medium/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=-Kapc68c","large":"16x9_large/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=Mjo-ZT4S","full":"16x9_full/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=ohIFDc-Q"},"square":{"tiny":"square_tiny/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=G5oZsqCF","small":"square_small/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=hsp0opFR","medium":"square_medium/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=lnqDbWT6","large":"square_large/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=voxtoV-v","full":"square_full/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=wfqx8zOx"},"article":{"tiny":"article_tiny/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=GMIRiQ2c","small":"article_small/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=7sDSOw7o","medium":"article_medium/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=XvKVYFUS","large":"article_large/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=h_kiwHxw","full":"article_full/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=eaMGMb4J"},"2x1":{"tiny":"2x1_tiny/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=mEb6tgej","small":"2x1_small/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=WIvx21Qt","medium":"2x1_medium/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=5Rw5hFvn","large":"2x1_large/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=3EaGWqB5","full":"2x1_full/public/Geopolitical%20Calendar%20Display%2002212025%20%281%29.png?itok=T_k0z6re"}}},"teaser_body":"Stay informed about the significant meetings and events RANE analysts are tracking.","pov":"","mailout":"Stay informed about the significant meetings and events RANE analysts are tracking.","overview":"","youtube_video_url":"","created":"1771014134","created_formatted":"Feb 13, 2026 | 20:22 GMT","changed":"1771014134","changed_formatted":"Feb 13, 2026 | 20:22 GMT","path_alias":"article/geopolitical-calendar","article_type":{"tid":"502","vid":"30","name":"Assessments"},"assessments_type":[],"column_type":[],"media_type":[],"global_perspectives_type":[],"sectioned_content_type":[],"forecast_type":[],"www_public_postings_type":[],"source":"","www_site_page_type":[],"taxonomy":[],"author":[],"pdf":"","status":1,"premium":1,"is_bookmarked":0},{"nid":"352002","type":"article","ntype":"worldview","title":"The Strategic Risks of Europe's Pivot to U.S. LNG","promo_image":{"uri":"public://GettyImages-2247701286.jpg","alt":"The U.S. and the EU flags are seen side by side on Nov. 21, 2025, in Brussels, Belgium. ","title":"The U.S. and the EU flags are seen side by side on Nov. 21, 2025, in Brussels, Belgium. ","caption":"The U.S. and the EU flags are seen side by side on Nov. 21, 2025, in Brussels, Belgium.","credit":"(Thierry Monasse/Getty Images)","sizes":{"16x9":{"tiny":"16x9_tiny/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=ZpQbGgOO","small":"16x9_small/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=a-ofPpQV","medium":"16x9_medium/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=349WVSDP","large":"16x9_large/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=cHbEPVG7","full":"16x9_full/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=zT6CaQff"},"square":{"tiny":"square_tiny/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=cCTqAJhV","small":"square_small/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=6nC3d0u6","medium":"square_medium/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=vphNwoKT","large":"square_large/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=9f6i6CrA","full":"square_full/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=VL6La5yM"},"article":{"tiny":"article_tiny/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=28HTTvXF","small":"article_small/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=UWqKqgbH","medium":"article_medium/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=87GO1Y-f","large":"article_large/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=YVCvfoJH","full":"article_full/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=09kwAR8G"},"2x1":{"tiny":"2x1_tiny/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=9ZezKyP6","small":"2x1_small/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=JqWWQMa1","medium":"2x1_medium/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=njDZZ8-7","large":"2x1_large/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=Lc8AP3IP","full":"2x1_full/public/GettyImages-2247701286.jpg?itok=PllSngwr"}}},"teaser_body":"By replacing Russian gas with U.S. LNG, the EU risks becoming reliant on another systemically central external supplier at a time of growing geopolitical instability and transatlantic tension.","pov":"","mailout":"By replacing Russian gas with U.S. LNG, the European Union risks swapping a strategic dependence on Moscow for one on Washington -- a relationship that, though fundamentally different, would not be immune to the use of energy as a tool of political and economic leverage, and that could leave the bloc operating with tighter market buffers and greater price volatility through the end of the decade, even as diversification reduces single-supplier risk. On Jan. 26, EU energy ministers approved legislation to phase out imports of Russian pipeline gas and liquefied natural gas (LNG) by the end of 2027. The phased ban will begin taking effect six weeks after it enters into force and tighten progressively through 2027, requiring companies to unwind existing agreements within defined timelines or face financial penalties. Spot imports of Russian gas and LNG will be prohibited six weeks after publication. Russian LNG imports under short-term contracts concluded before June 2025 will be banned from April 2026, while imports under long-term LNG contracts will be banned from January 2027. Pipeline gas imports under short-term contracts concluded before June 2025 will also be banned from June 2026, while imports under long-term contracts will be phased out from September 2027, with extensions possible until November 2027 if EU member states are not on track to meet gas storage targets. Russian oil imports are not covered under the approved package, though the European Commission has indicated it plans to submit additional legislation later this year to also prohibit Russian oil imports by the end of 2027.","overview":"","youtube_video_url":"","created":"1770931237","created_formatted":"Feb 12, 2026 | 21:20 GMT","changed":"1770931341","changed_formatted":"Feb 12, 2026 | 21:22 GMT","path_alias":"article/strategic-risks-europes-pivot-us-lng","article_type":{"tid":"502","vid":"30","name":"Assessments"},"assessments_type":[],"column_type":[],"media_type":[],"global_perspectives_type":[],"sectioned_content_type":[],"forecast_type":[],"www_public_postings_type":[],"source":"","www_site_page_type":[],"taxonomy":[{"tid":"59","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"United States","code":"US","path_alias":"/region/americas/united-states"},{"tid":"21","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Europe","code":"","path_alias":"/region/europe"},{"tid":"526","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Energy","path_alias":"/topic/energy"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","v_name":"wv_topics","name":"Politics","path_alias":"/topic/politics"}],"author":[],"pdf":"","status":1,"premium":1,"countries":[{"tid":"59","vid":"5","name":"United States"},{"tid":"21","vid":"5","name":"Europe"}],"wv_topics":[{"tid":"526","vid":"33","name":"Energy"},{"tid":"530","vid":"33","name":"Politics"}],"is_bookmarked":0},{"nid":"351972","type":"article","ntype":"worldview","title":"Economic Concessions to U.S. Offer Path for Regime Survival in Cuba","promo_image":{"uri":"public://GettyImages-2260228972.jpg","alt":"American Airlines planes sit on the tarmac at Jose Marti International Airport in Havana on Feb. 9, 2026. ","title":"American Airlines planes sit on the tarmac at Jose Marti International Airport in Havana on Feb. 9, 2026. ","caption":"American Airlines planes sit on the tarmac at Jose Marti International Airport in Havana on Feb. 9, 2026. ","credit":"(YAMIL LAGE/AFP via Getty Images)","sizes":{"16x9":{"tiny":"16x9_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=-jmoWiDX","small":"16x9_small/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=5353kHUl","medium":"16x9_medium/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=2gja2f6S","large":"16x9_large/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=Li0IgqY-","full":"16x9_full/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=so9AwDdc"},"square":{"tiny":"square_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=MoWCH8yR","small":"square_small/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=oOeQQqaP","medium":"square_medium/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=SWdj_kqQ","large":"square_large/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=_Iuw4E5g","full":"square_full/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=5_sd8lXR"},"article":{"tiny":"article_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=aOgmjH_l","small":"article_small/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=ykVI-RHl","medium":"article_medium/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=aIgO_PTk","large":"article_large/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=uhZIpEWl","full":"article_full/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=1Oqfi0n-"},"2x1":{"tiny":"2x1_tiny/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=G_aE7MGI","small":"2x1_small/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=lHSgB0gs","medium":"2x1_medium/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=k0elTWVc","large":"2x1_large/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=5fHCHHd8","full":"2x1_full/public/GettyImages-2260228972.jpg?itok=pLyr6qVF"}}},"teaser_body":"Facing imminent economic collapse and the loss of key allies, the Cuban government will likely yield to U.S. demands for market liberalization to avoid a total breakdown of state authority while attempting to preserve political control.","pov":"","mailout":"Facing imminent collapse and mounting U.S. pressure, the Cuban government will likely make concessions to Washington to gradually open its economy without requiring structural political changes, which the United States will likely support to avoid a state collapse and reaffirm its geopolitical dominance in the Western Hemisphere.","overview":"","youtube_video_url":"","created":"1770749346","created_formatted":"Feb 10, 2026 | 18:49 GMT","changed":"1770826465","changed_formatted":"Feb 11, 2026 | 16:14 GMT","path_alias":"article/economic-concessions-us-offer-path-regime-survival-cuba","article_type":{"tid":"502","vid":"30","name":"Assessments"},"assessments_type":[],"column_type":[],"media_type":[],"global_perspectives_type":[],"sectioned_content_type":[],"forecast_type":[],"www_public_postings_type":[],"source":"","www_site_page_type":[],"taxonomy":[{"tid":"39","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Cuba","code":"CU","path_alias":"/region/americas/cuba"},{"tid":"49","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"Mexico","code":"MX","path_alias":"/region/americas/mexico"},{"tid":"59","vid":"5","v_name":"countries","name":"United St